The paper discusses the development of an efficient and secure routing protocol for wireless sensor networks, which involves the use of signal to noise ratio (SNR)-based power control and handoff-based self-recovery mechanisms. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and network security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data processing and optimization techniques (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and control systems (cs.SY) to improve the performance of the routing protocol.
